There are fears that a serial killer is on the loose in a Lady Frere village in the Eastern Cape. Another pensioner was gruesomely murdered on Friday. 18 people have been killed in 7 months, with 11 of them being elderly. Daily Dispatch senior reporter Lulamile Feni unpacks this further on #eNCA. courtesy #DStv403 LADY FRERE - There are fears a serial killer may be on the loose in a Lady Frere village in the Eastern Cape. This follows the gruesome murder of a pensioner on Friday. 18 people have been killed in the area in 7 months. READ: Six family members killed in Eastern Cape Of those killed, 11 of them were elderly people. But no arrests have been made. Watch the video above for more details on this story